# WHAT IT IS
#   emtt is a single-purpose long-lived daemon: it speaks the
#   Meshtastic node-protocol's syslog egress (typically
#   `0.0.0.0:50514`) and forwards every received text /
#   broadcast / channel message into a configured Telegram
#   chat via a Telegram Bot.  Useful for relaying off-grid
#   LoRa mesh radio chatter to a managed Telegram group / DM
#   inbox.
#
#   Configuration is dual-mode:  every flag has a `TELEGRAM_*`
#   / `SYSLOG_*` / `MESH_*` / `LOG_LEVEL` / `WEBHOOK_URL` /
#   `PROXY_URL` env-var equivalent (clap `env` attribute).
#   Message rendering uses a minijinja template
#   (`--template`) that interpolates Meshtastic-decoded fields
#   like `from`, `via`, `text`, `snr`, `rssi`, `hops_away`;
#   the default template is `<b>{{ from }}</b> (via
#   <i>{{ via }}</i>)\n<blockquote>{{ text }}</blockquote>`
#   rendered as Telegram HTML.
#
#   `--parse-mode` switches between Telegram's HTML and
#   MarkdownV2 formatters; `--proxy-url` enables SOCKS-/
#   HTTPS-proxied Telegram-API egress; `--api-server` points
#   at a self-hosted Bot API server (useful when fronting
#   `api.telegram.org` via a local Tor / Wireguard endpoint).
#   The `--webhook-url` flag accepts an additional generic-
#   webhook destination that emtt POSTs the same JSON payload
#   to in parallel (for chaining into Home Assistant
#   notifications, Slack, Discord, etc.).
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/main.rs clap-derive
#                       `Cli` struct + `Commands::Syslog`
#                       variant; extracted via `gh api
#                       repos/black-roland/emtt/contents/src/
#                       main.rs`)
#
#   emtt [GLOBAL OPTIONS] syslog [OPTIONS]
#
#   Global persistent flags:
#     -l, --log-level <LEVEL>        Log level
#                                    (error | warn | info |
#                                     debug | trace)
#                                    [env: LOG_LEVEL;
#                                     default: debug]
#
#   Subcommand:
#     syslog                         Run in syslog-bridge mode
#                                    (the only command — the
#                                    daemon listens on the
#                                    configured syslog UDP
#                                    port and forwards parsed
#                                    Meshtastic messages to
#                                    Telegram)
#
#       Telegram destination:
#         --bot-token <TOKEN>          Telegram bot token
#                                      [env: TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN]
#         --chat-id <N>                Telegram chat ID
#                                      (negative for
#                                      supergroups / channels)
#                                      [env: TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID]
#         --api-server <URL>           Self-hosted Bot API
#                                      server URL
#                                      [env:
#                                      TELEGRAM_API_SERVER]
#
#       Message rendering:
#         --template <TPL>             minijinja message
#                                      template
#                                      [env: TELEGRAM_TEMPLATE
#                                       default: <b>{{ from
#                                       }}</b> (via <i>{{ via
#                                       }}</i>)\n<blockquote>
#                                       {{ text }}</blockquote>]
#         --parse-mode <MODE>          Telegram parse mode
#                                      [env:
#                                      TELEGRAM_PARSE_MODE;
#                                      default: html]
#                                      (html | markdown |
#                                       markdown-v2)
#
#       Meshtastic ingress:
#         --syslog-host <HOST>         UDP listen host
#                                      [env: SYSLOG_HOST;
#                                      default: 0.0.0.0]
#         --syslog-port <PORT>         UDP listen port
#                                      [env: SYSLOG_PORT;
#                                      default: 50514]
